1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,254
[Guerzon] <i>It was Manuel</i>
<i>who killed your parents, Lara.</i>

2
00:00:04,337 --> 00:00:07,048
- [gunshots]
<i>- He was the mastermind behind that attack.</i>

3
00:00:07,757 --> 00:00:10,593
[Lara]
<i>You've kept so many secrets from me, Dad.</i>

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,262
<i>I'll make you pay.</i>

5
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:14,389
You killed my parents, didn't you?!

6
00:00:14,472 --> 00:00:15,765
- [Lara] You're insane!
- Lara!

7
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,603
Don't. Don't do it.

8
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:25,775
- [Manuel crying]
- [gunshots]

9
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,902
[Manuel and Felix crying]

10
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:34,034
Lara…

11
00:00:35,285 --> 00:00:39,289
[Teresa] <i>Maybe I'm just hoping</i>
<i>that my son is still alive.</i>

12
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:41,082
<i>I have to try.</i>

13
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:42,709
<i>I need answers.</i>

14
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:44,919
<i>Where is it?</i>

15
00:00:45,003 --> 00:00:48,256
[Emil] <i>Agent Angeles was found last night</i>
<i>in front of the NLEA.</i>

16
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:50,800
<i>Wrapped in a body bag.</i>

17
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:51,885
<i>Dead!</i>

18
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,678
Who would do this to Agent Angeles?

19
00:00:53,762 --> 00:00:56,556
[Ethan]
<i>We already checked the CCTV footage.</i>

20
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:58,975
- [Jalil] <i>Did you find anything?</i>
- [Buster] <i>Nothing, sir.</i>

21
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,352
The body bag was dropped in a blind spot.

22
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:04,147
<i>Whoever left it there seems</i>
<i>to know the entire perimeter.</i>

23
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:07,317
[Manuel] <i>So whoever did this,</i>
<i>you'd better be ready.</i>

24
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,235
<i>I won't stop</i>

25
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:13,406
until you pay for what you've done!

26
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:16,326
I know that… you love Lara.

27
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,911
<i>But because of what you did…</i>

28
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:22,123
<i>you've proven your loyalty to me.</i>

29
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:32,425
[theme music playing]

30
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:45,772
[melancholic music playing]

31
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:00,995
[exhales deeply]

32
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,792
[melancholic music continues]

33
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,548
[Manuel gasps]

34
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,759
- Teresa.
- My condolences, General.

35
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:17,846
Thank you.

36
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,432
It's heartbreaking what happened.

37
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:26,312
Lara and Marcus were together
for so long that…

38
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:28,690
she felt like a daughter to me too.

39
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:31,401
Mm.

40
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:34,529
I understand
what you're going through, General.

41
00:02:35,196 --> 00:02:37,866
You know I've lost a child as well.

42
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,787
I hope whoever did this pays for it.

43
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:47,000
I hope so too, Teresa.

44
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,293
I hope so.

45
00:02:48,376 --> 00:02:51,588
[music becomes dark]

46
00:02:57,093 --> 00:02:58,177
My condolences, General.

47
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:01,681
Thank you.

48
00:03:06,227 --> 00:03:08,187
- My condolences, sir.
- Thank you.

49
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:13,234
[dark music continues]

50
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:15,987
- My condolences, General.
- [Manuel] Thank you.

51
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:21,951
- My condolences, sir.
- Thank you.

52
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:26,289
- My condolences, sir.
- Thank you.

53
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:28,833
- My condolences, sir.
- Thank you.

54
00:03:29,417 --> 00:03:30,376
[Manuel] Thank you.

55
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:34,589
Thank you so much.

56
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:38,968
Please excuse me for a moment.

57
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:46,184
[dark music continues]

58
00:03:46,768 --> 00:03:48,144
- Our condolences.
- Sir.

59
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,145
Thank you.

60
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,481
- My condolences, sir.
- Thank you.

61
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:52,899
[Manuel] Please, have a seat.

62
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:03,910
[melancholic music playing]

63
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:19,217
[Lara] <i>Come on, at least buy me a coffee!</i>

64
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:21,886
[Marcus] <i>You already miss me that much?</i>

65
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:24,013
<i>You really can't stand</i>
<i>being away from me, huh?</i>

66
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:25,848
You don't need to thank me.

67
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:27,684
It's okay, really.

68
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:33,064
[melancholic music continues]

69
00:04:53,167 --> 00:04:54,460
[Marcus] <i>Goodbye, Lara.</i>

70
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:59,048
[melancholic music continues]

71
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:28,411
[melancholic music continues]

72
00:05:38,629 --> 00:05:43,259
[Jalil] <i>May Allah grant you peace</i>
<i>in the afterlife.</i>

73
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:46,888
<i>Goodbye, Agent Angeles.</i>

74
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:50,516
[melancholic music continues]

75
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,610
General Carillo, our deepest condolences.

76
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:02,904
Thank you very much.

77
00:06:02,987 --> 00:06:06,449
I do understand
this is a very difficult time for you.

78
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:07,700
And I will understand

79
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:10,787
if you want to reschedule
your live interview.

80
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:11,788
No.

81
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:16,084
I want to speak up… ̀for Lara.

82
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:20,046
Because I know that's what
she would've wanted me to do for her.

83
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:22,131
[indistinct dialogue]

84
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:24,675
[Maya] Thank you, General.

85
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,427
[morose music playing]

86
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:35,019
[morose music playing]

87
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:55,164
[morose music continues]

88
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:02,922
[glum music playing]

89
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,257
Cuchy…

90
00:07:05,424 --> 00:07:07,218
Madam is no longer with us.

91
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:13,808
Come here. Give me a hug.

92
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:20,898
[glum music continues]

93
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,862
I told her so many times,
but she didn't listen to me.

94
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,030
But what can I do?

95
00:07:30,324 --> 00:07:32,952
I didn't want General Carillo to kill me.

96
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,081
I'm going to miss her.

97
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:41,919
[sighs]

98
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:45,965
Lara…

99
00:07:48,384 --> 00:07:49,343
Lara…

100
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,763
Wherever you are…

101
00:07:57,185 --> 00:07:58,186
I'm sorry.

102
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:04,233
[glum music continues]

103
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:16,787
I don't believe General Carillo
had nothing to do with this.

104
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:20,333
That's impossible.

105
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:24,462
But we don't have
any evidence against him.

106
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:27,757
And now he's gaining
the people's sympathy.

107
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:33,346
We just have to keep investigating.

108
00:08:33,429 --> 00:08:34,847
We'll find something.

109
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:37,683
Reyes is right.

110
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:40,686
You need to stay close to the General.

111
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:44,398
Find out his whereabouts.

112
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,692
Okay, sir.

113
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:48,110
So what's our plan now?

114
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:52,114
[pensive music playing]

115
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,920
I watched Maya Mae Kalaw's documentary.

116
00:09:06,003 --> 00:09:08,714
Apparently, Mustapha and General Carillo

117
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:10,466
are going to face each other
in a live interview.

118
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,718
That's your chance.

119
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,720
After that,

120
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:19,141
they'll definitely move forward
with all their evil plans.

121
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:22,895
[pensive music continues]

122
00:09:30,027 --> 00:09:33,322
Did you notice those subtle glances
between General Carillo and Felix earlier?

123
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:34,574
Yes.

124
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:36,909
It felt like they meant something.

125
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:38,619
Do you think…

126
00:09:39,537 --> 00:09:43,291
Felix has anything to do
with what the General's been doing?

127
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:47,712
I don't know yet.

128
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:52,550
But starting now, we need
to keep Felix under surveillance.

129
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:53,759
You're right.

130
00:09:54,969 --> 00:10:00,266
We don't know
which of our colleagues we can trust.

131
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:02,810
[pensive music continues]

132
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,234
Lara was so young.

133
00:10:11,319 --> 00:10:12,862
How are you holding up, son?

134
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:15,197
I know you and Lara were very close.

135
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:17,491
You two went through a lot together.

136
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:20,995
I know this isn't easy for you.

137
00:10:22,872 --> 00:10:25,750
I still can't believe Lara's gone.

138
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:29,503
[pensive music playing]

139
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,130
The truth is, Ma…

140
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,925
Lara and I had a falling out.

141
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:37,970
We weren't on good terms.

142
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:41,390
Why? What happened?

143
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,439
I lost my trust in her.

144
00:10:49,523 --> 00:10:51,192
I started suspecting her.

145
00:10:52,401 --> 00:10:53,611
So did Espina.

146
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:56,113
We both believed General Carillo

147
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,948
was behind everything
that's been happening.

148
00:10:58,032 --> 00:11:01,494
And that General Carillo also had
something to do with Lara's death.

149
00:11:01,577 --> 00:11:02,620
What?

150
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:07,625
How could a parent do something like that
to their own child?

151
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,960
[pensive music continues]

152
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:22,139
[gentle music playing]

153
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:25,768
[man] Cogeo! Still plenty of seats!

154
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:29,271
Cogeo! Cogeo! Cogeo!

155
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:32,733
Uncle! Why don't you take a break?
I'll take over for now.

156
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:36,028
Perfect timing!
I was getting thirsty anyway.

157
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,488
[knocking on window]

158
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:40,491
Cogeo! Cogeo, Padilla!

159
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,577
Hop in, we're leaving!

160
00:11:43,661 --> 00:11:45,079
Cogeo!

161
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:46,205
[mini bus door closes]

162
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:47,790
Hey, miss! Welcome.

163
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,375
- Oh!
- Come on in.

164
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,793
- Why are you here?
- [Eve] Pa!

165
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:52,795
I left food for you at home.

166
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:55,297
Yeah, but it's boring eating alone.

167
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,674
Cogeo!

168
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:57,883
- We're about to--
- There you go again, Eve.

169
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,511
You're already a cop.
Quit working as a barker.

170
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:01,804
Why, Pa?

171
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:04,265
It's not like
I didn't do this for you before.

172
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:05,599
That was then.

173
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:07,893
Look at that.

174
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:10,855
The bus gets filled
when I'm the one calling for passengers.

175
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:13,941
You know,
they'll still ride the same bus, dear.

176
00:12:14,024 --> 00:12:17,278
What are you even doing?
You've only gotten a break from work now.

177
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:19,655
Shouldn't you just be relaxing at home?

178
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:21,991
I just missed you, Dad.

179
00:12:22,783 --> 00:12:24,618
[Eve] Okay, I could just rest.

180
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:26,662
But I wouldn't be with you
because you're working.

181
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:28,622
So, I just came here.

182
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:30,082
Right?

183
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:32,126
Okay, fine. I'll get to work now.

184
00:12:32,209 --> 00:12:34,962
- Okay. Mm.
- It's all right. Just leave this to me.

185
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:37,047
Go, Dad! Let's go!

186
00:12:37,965 --> 00:12:39,383
Cogeo!

187
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:42,928
[pensive music playing]

188
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,430
What a day.

189
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:49,768
[Eve] Cogeo, Padilla! Hop in.

190
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,939
Cogeo!

191
00:12:54,648 --> 00:12:56,567
Cogeo, let's go. Good morning!

192
00:12:56,650 --> 00:13:00,613
[phone ringing]

193
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,410
Jamilah? What is it?

194
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:07,995
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil…</i>

195
00:13:08,078 --> 00:13:09,955
I just wanted to check on you.

196
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:12,791
I just heard what happened to…

197
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,543
<i>your teammate Lara Angeles.</i>

198
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,462
Why was she killed?

199
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:19,590
We're still figuring it out.

200
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:21,926
[Jalil] <i>Why are you asking?</i>

201
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:24,470
- Father? Father!
- [gasps] Jamilah…

202
00:13:25,095 --> 00:13:27,264
- Go on! I'll hurt him!
- Don't hurt Father!

203
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:28,349
Shut up!

204
00:13:28,432 --> 00:13:30,392
Don't come near us or I'll kill him!

205
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:33,062
[Jamilah] Uh…

206
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:36,273
I'm just worried about you, Jalil.

207
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,859
Jamilah, don't worry about me.

208
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:40,861
I can take care of myself.

209
00:13:40,945 --> 00:13:42,446
How is Father doing?

210
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:46,325
[Datu Rahman] My child, please.

211
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:51,580
Let me tell Jalil
about all of this myself.

212
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,957
[Jamilah exhales sharply]

213
00:13:54,458 --> 00:13:56,669
Father is doing well.

214
00:13:56,752 --> 00:13:59,463
Jalil, why don't you pay Father a visit?

215
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,465
It sounds like you have
a lot to talk about.

216
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:03,592
He also told me that.

217
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:06,136
He wanted to chat with me.

218
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:10,266
But I still have a lot of work
to do right now.

219
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:13,394
It's also dangerous
if someone sees us together.

220
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:15,437
I don't know
if someone's keeping an eye on me.

221
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:17,356
I understand, Jalil.

222
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:18,941
Be careful.

223
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:22,319
You too, okay? Jamilah, be careful, okay?

224
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,655
[foreboding music playing]

225
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:27,992
[exhales deeply]

226
00:14:36,667 --> 00:14:38,085
[phone chimes]

227
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:40,838
I'M ON MY WAY

228
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:47,845
ME TOO

229
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:57,313
Okay, man.

230
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,166
[Edrick] We're here, sir.

231
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:20,419
Sir Mustapha is backstage.

232
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:22,129
What about General Carillo?

233
00:15:22,212 --> 00:15:23,172
He's also on the way, sir.

234
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:26,008
Sir, what's going to happen?

235
00:15:26,675 --> 00:15:28,344
Don't ask too many questions.

236
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:30,888
It's better if you know nothing.

237
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:34,767
Because I have no legal background?

238
00:15:37,019 --> 00:15:39,355
Okay, sir. I'll get back to work.

239
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,815
That's because
your background is illegal, isn't it?

240
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:43,359
Okay, get back to work.

241
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,239
[assistant director]
Okay, guys, last 15 minutes!

242
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:50,658
Go, go, go, let's go!

243
00:15:50,741 --> 00:15:51,992
Pearly, go.

244
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:58,874
Five. Four. Three. Two…

245
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:02,378
We can no longer turn a blind eye

246
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:05,214
to the growing number
of violent incidents,

247
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:07,883
deaths, and criminality

248
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:12,221
that is caused by the continuous
dispersal of illegal weapons.

249
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:14,348
Who's to blame?

250
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:16,433
[Maya] Is this problem systemic?

251
00:16:16,517 --> 00:16:20,270
Is the problem
with a lack of law enforcement

252
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:24,942
or is there a bigger reason
that we have not seen yet?

253
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:28,862
Tonight, join me as we find out

254
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:30,698
the answers to these questions.

255
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:35,369
This is Maya Mae Kalaw.
Inside the Truth Live.

256
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:37,788
[Maya] And to shed light on the questions

257
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:39,790
we all have on our minds,

258
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:43,585
please welcome
two of the most important personalities

259
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,963
on the issue of national security.

260
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:50,134
The first-ever director
of the Special Investigations Division,

261
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:53,679
retired Police General Manuel Carillo.

262
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:58,809
And the Presidential Chief of Staff,
Mr. Ahmad Mustapha.

263
00:16:58,892 --> 00:17:00,269
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

264
00:17:01,228 --> 00:17:03,814
[foreboding music playing]

265
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,279
Gentlemen…

266
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:25,919
[foreboding music continues]

267
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:27,880
First of all,

268
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:31,258
we'd like to thank General Carillo first

269
00:17:31,341 --> 00:17:34,303
for making the time
to be in this interview

270
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:38,015
despite the recent passing
of his daughter, Agent Lara Angeles.

271
00:17:38,682 --> 00:17:39,767
[chuckles softly]

272
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,186
It's okay. It's uh…

273
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:47,066
Actually, it's my way
of honoring my daughter's life.

274
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:51,195
[Manuel] By continuing to live.

275
00:17:51,278 --> 00:17:56,325
And by doing my duty
of keeping everyone safe

276
00:17:56,408 --> 00:18:02,164
by calling attention
to this widespread lawlessness.

277
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:03,665
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

278
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:07,628
To God we belong
and to Him we shall return.

279
00:18:09,338 --> 00:18:13,926
Please accept my deepest sympathies,
General.

280
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:16,095
Thank you.

281
00:18:19,723 --> 00:18:22,601
[tense music playing]

282
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:31,819
Stay alert.

283
00:18:31,902 --> 00:18:33,946
Things are getting heated.

284
00:18:36,031 --> 00:18:39,118
The first thing I want to ask you both is,

285
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:42,788
our country has
very strict gun control policies,

286
00:18:42,871 --> 00:18:46,125
so why does the proliferation
of illegal firearms continue?

287
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,543
[Mustapha] You're right.

288
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:52,589
Our country has
very strict gun control laws.

289
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:55,759
But the problem
is not the lack of policies,

290
00:18:55,843 --> 00:19:02,015
it is the importation of illegal weapons.

291
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,519
We don't know where they come from.

292
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:08,730
We don't know whose hands they end up in.

293
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:10,399
And to make things worse,

294
00:19:10,482 --> 00:19:15,571
there appears to be an NLEA insider
protecting this operation.

295
00:19:16,363 --> 00:19:20,784
The agency that should be
taking down these syndicates

296
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,453
is actually protecting them instead.

297
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:27,666
As a result,
the crime rate continues to rise.

298
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:33,297
People have lost trust
in the police, in the government.

299
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:36,967
They no longer feel safe.

300
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:40,929
But the two police officers
who are alleged members

301
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:43,932
of the gun smuggling syndicate
were arrested already, weren't they?

302
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,601
You're right.

303
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:48,270
Yes, these suspects were apprehended,

304
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:52,482
but catching them
doesn't solve the problem.

305
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:54,234
This is a massive operation.

306
00:19:54,902 --> 00:19:56,403
What do you mean?

307
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:58,614
What if their plan

308
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:02,910
all along… is to bring chaos?

309
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:06,872
To plunge the country into chaos.

310
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:11,293
Why would they do that?

311
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,589
Destabilization.

312
00:20:16,173 --> 00:20:18,467
[tense music continues]

313
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:20,636
Are you saying

314
00:20:21,303 --> 00:20:24,264
there are agencies trying
to overthrow the government?

315
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,311
Miss Mae,

316
00:20:30,103 --> 00:20:33,565
I believe the General can explain it best,

317
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:35,859
since he is the expert.

318
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:41,323
Sir Mustapha is so brave.

319
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:42,908
- Yes.
- He is.

320
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,994
[tense music continues]

321
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:59,424
[Mustapha] <i>It's all connected.</i>

322
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:01,510
<i>This isn't just about money.</i>

323
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:04,054
<i>They are working towards a goal.</i>

324
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:06,306
<i>Well, maybe you should look into it.</i>

325
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:10,102
[sighs sharply] If there truly are
attempts to destabilize the country,

326
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:11,728
they should be stopped.

327
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:16,775
General Carillo, what do you think?

328
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:18,819
<i>Do you think this syndicate</i>

329
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:20,779
is simply involved in gun trafficking

330
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:25,534
or do they want
to overthrow the government?

331
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,246
I haven't thought about that.

332
00:21:29,329 --> 00:21:32,082
We will discuss this
with the Security Council.

333
00:21:32,165 --> 00:21:37,504
[tense music continues]

334
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:47,889
[Maya] <i>The massacre on Damai Island,</i>

335
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:50,225
<i>the bank robbery, the school shooting,</i>

336
00:21:50,309 --> 00:21:54,938
<i>the hostage taking,</i>
<i>the bombing targeting Japanese tourists,</i>

337
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:59,401
<i>now, the recent death</i>
<i>of Agent Lara Angeles,</i>

338
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:01,111
are they all connected?

339
00:22:02,237 --> 00:22:05,657
My daughter Lara was one of the casualties

340
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:11,913
<i>of all of this chaos.</i>

341
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:17,502
Crimes nowadays have
simply gotten out of hand.

342
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:20,672
Injustice continues to prevail.

343
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:23,300
[Mustapha] General, with all due respect,

344
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:28,972
don't forget that all of this started

345
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:33,894
long before the hostage-taking happened.

346
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:39,775
There is a bigger reason
this is happening.

347
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,613
Mustapha knows what he's doing.

348
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:48,784
That’s why
many in our community look up to him.

349
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,452
[Maya] <i>Can you please expound, sir?</i>

350
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:51,661
[Mustapha] <i>Miss Mae,</i>

351
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:56,083
it all started with the explosion…

352
00:22:56,166 --> 00:22:58,460
[tense music continues]

353
00:22:58,543 --> 00:23:01,922
…on the MV Doña Emilia.

354
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:05,634
[tense music swells]

355
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:23,652
It was carrying illegal firearms

356
00:23:23,735 --> 00:23:26,071
<i>and exploded</i>
<i>before it could be apprehended.</i>

357
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:30,951
My silence protects no one but myself.

358
00:23:31,034 --> 00:23:32,077
What's your plan?

359
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,455
I will tell him the truth, Omar.
Even if it's hard.

360
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:39,584
They're the reason I lost Gabriel!

361
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:43,630
Are you positive it wasn't an accident?

362
00:23:43,713 --> 00:23:45,382
Why do you ask?

363
00:23:45,465 --> 00:23:46,842
I lost my brother in that explosion, sir.

364
00:23:47,425 --> 00:23:50,637
Mustapha has figured it out.
He has to die!

365
00:23:53,348 --> 00:23:54,933
What happened?

366
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:58,520
Someone's following Sir Mustapha.
His life's in danger.

367
00:23:58,603 --> 00:24:00,939
[engines rev]

368
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,983
[Mustapha] <i>Get ready.</i>
<i>We're in for a fight.</i>

369
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:06,403
[gunshot]

370
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:09,239
[rapid gunfire]

371
00:24:09,322 --> 00:24:11,074
[tires screech]

372
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:12,868
[explosion]

373
00:24:13,451 --> 00:24:15,287
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you.

374
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:17,330
Thank you, Agent Marcus.
